Icelandic air traffic controllers
have begun diverting international air traffic to fly south of
the north Atlantic island, Hjordis Gudmundsdottir, spokeswoman
for ISAVIA Ltd., told local broadcaster RUV. An ash plume from a
volcanic eruption by Grimsvotn, underneath Vatnajokull Glacier,
has now reached 50,000 feet.  To contact the reporter on this story:
